Moving average smoothing practice

data("AirPassengers")
m3 = filter(AirPassengers, filter=rep(1/3,3)) # 1/3 
m6 = filter(AirPassengers, filter=rep(1/6,6))
m12 = filter(AirPassengers, filter=rep(1/12,12))

#(+) -    
plot(AirPassengers, main="AirPassengers: original data") 

plot(m3, main="3-point moving average")

plot(m6, main="6-point moving average")

plot(m12, main="12-point moving average") #

R example : 4point MA for dd1

library(forecast)
## Registered S3 method overwritten by 'quantmod':
##   method            from
##   as.zoo.data.frame zoo
dd1 = matrix(c(1342,1442,1252,1343,1425,1362,1456,1272,1243,
               1359,1412,1253,1201,1478,1322,1406,1254,1289,1497,1208))
dd1.ts = ts(data=dd1, start=c(2006,1), frequency=4)
dd1.ts
##      Qtr1 Qtr2 Qtr3 Qtr4
## 2006 1342 1442 1252 1343
## 2007 1425 1362 1456 1272
## 2008 1243 1359 1412 1253
## 2009 1201 1478 1322 1406
## 2010 1254 1289 1497 1208
ff=filter(dd1.ts, filter=rep(1,4)/4, method="convolution", sides=1) # - 2006   3 NA
plot(dd1.ts, main="dd1.ts with simple moving average smoothing") +
  lines(ff, col="red", lty=2, lwd=2) + #red; 
  abline(h=mean(dd1), col="blue") #blue; dd1 data 

## integer(0)
# - smoothing   dd1.ts  :     
res=ff[-1:-3,]-dd1.ts[-1:-3,] #ff: 2006 3   dd1.ts  
tsdisplay(res, main="Residuals by MA(4) for dd1") # , ACF, PACF  

                                                  #     .
Box.test(res, type="Box-Pierce") #:TS is independent( )
## 
##  Box-Pierce test
## 
## data:  res
## X-squared = 0.97729, df = 1, p-value = 0.3229
                                 #p-value 0.3229   .
                                 #,

double moving average smoothing (==)

ff1 = filter(dd1.ts, filter=rep(1,3)/3, method="convolution", sides=1)
ff2 = filter(ff1, filter=rep(1,3)/3, method="convolution", sides=1) # smoothing

plot(dd1.ts, main="dd1.ts with simple moving average smoothing") +
  lines(ff2, col="red", lty=2, lwd=2) + #ff1  smoothing
  abline(h=mean(dd1), col="blue")

## integer(0)
res = ff2[-1:-3,]-dd1.ts[-1:-3,]
tsdisplay(res, main="Residuals by double MA smoothing")

Box.test(res, type="Box-Pierce") #H0 : TS is independent
## 
##  Box-Pierce test
## 
## data:  res
## X-squared = 1.0548, df = 1, p-value = 0.3044

double moving average(2nd method)

mm1 = ma(dd1.ts, order=4, centre=F) #    - t  4(t, t-1, t-2, t-3)
mm3 = ma(dd1.ts, order=3, centre=T) #    - t , 3(t-1, t, t+1)
mm4 = ma(mm3, order=3, centre=T) #

res3 = mm4-dd1.ts 
Box.test(res3)
## 
##  Box-Pierce test
## 
## data:  res3
## X-squared = 1.3138, df = 1, p-value = 0.2517
#forecast -  2 (h=2)
